subtotal.title: subtotal
subtotal.desc: Returns `properties.subtotal` and fallsback on a calculation based on `properties.total`, `properties.tax`, `properties.shipping` and `properties.discount`.

currency.title: currency
currency.desc: Returns the `properties.currency` and falls back on "USD"

referrer.title: referrer
referrer.desc: Returns the `context.referrer.url` and falls back in the order of `context.page.referrer` and `properties.referrer`.

properties.title: properties(aliases)
properties.desc: Returns the entire `properties` object. You can optionally pass an alias object.

username.title: username
username.desc: Returns the `traits.username` and falls back in the order of `properties.username`, `userId`, and `anonymousId`.

email.title: email
email.desc: Returns the `traits.email`, falling back on `properties.email` and `context.traits.email`. The last resort is to check if the `userId` passed in was a valid email. If it is, it will return that value.

revenue.title: revenue
revenue.desc: Returns the `properties.revenue`. However, if the event name is `Completed Order` (case insensitive), it will return the `properties.total`. The return value is always a `float`.
